etymologies: late 18th century; earliest use found in Thomas Taylor (1758–1835), philosopher and translator. From Hellenistic Greek ζωογόνος producing animals, generative, in Byzantine Greek also life-producing (Proclus; from ancient Greek ζωή life + -γονος producing) + -ic

definitions: Of or relating to the generation or development of animals or living things generally; life-producing, generative.
